main event: A civilian observer sighted a brightly colored disc-shaped object in the western sky of Cushing, Wisconsin, on February 25, 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as disc-shaped and glowing with all colors., A relative had seen a similar object the previous evening., The sighting was thought to be a planet, possibly Venus., The object was still visible when the observer went inside., The sighting lasted for about 25 minutes.
witness description: A female civilian about 20 years old and her mother, both residing in Cushing, Wisconsin.
